194
00:07:42,560 --> 00:07:45,440
Then anyway, its clock was suspended.

195
00:07:45,440 --> 00:07:48,500
So another node just elected a new leader, right?

196
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:52,280
The previously suspended master node has resumed execution, but the client is unaware that the master node has changed.

197
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:56,080
The client is unaware that the master node has changed.

198
00:07:56,080 --> 00:07:58,040
then send it to the old master node

199
00:07:58,040 --> 00:07:59,800
